I. INTRODUCTION

Named Entity Recognition (NER) is a basic and impor- tant task in Natural Language Processing (NLP). It aims to recognize and classify named entities, such as person names and location names[1]. Extracting named entities from unstructured data can benefit many NLP tasks, for example Knowledge Graph (KG), Decision-making Support System (DSS), and Question Answering system.
